Description:
The application contains a stock check feature that fetches data from an internal system.
This functionality is vulnerable to Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF), allowing access to internal resources.

Objective:
Access internal admin panel
Delete user: carlos

Tools Used:
Burp Suite (Proxy + Repeater)

Exploitation Steps:
1️-Intercept Request

Go to a product page
Click Check Stock
Intercept request using Burp Suite

2️-Send to Repeater

Forward the request to Burp Repeater
Locate parameter:
stockApi

3️-Access Admin Panel

Modify the request:
stockApi=http://localhost/admin

This reveals the internal admin interface.

4️-Find Delete Endpoint

From the response HTML:
http://localhost/admin/delete?username=carlos

5️-Exploit SSRF

Update the request:

stockApi=http://localhost/admin/delete?username=carlos

Result:

Gained access to internal admin panel
Successfully deleted user carlos
